<figureCitation box="[724,821,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="36.[151,269,1661,1685]" captionTargetBox="[199,1384,202,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-73@36.[195,1392,194,1637]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Adults of Megalota. 1. M. submicans (holotype), 2. M. synchysis (paratype), 3. M. peruviana (paratype), 4. M. aquilonaris (holotype), 5. M. vulgaris (paratype), 6. M. cacaulana (holotype), 7. M. macrosocia (holotype), 8. M. ochreoapex (holotype), 9. M. spinulosa (holotype), 10. M. simpliciana (paratype), 11. M. delphinosema (Costa Rica), 12. M. jamaicana (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307542/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[833,862,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–36" captionStartId="41.[151,269,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,178,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-52@41.[190,1398,144,2009]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 34–36. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 34. M. simpliciana, image of USNM slide 85,851; 35. M. delphinosema, image of USNM slide 84,895; 36. M. jamaicana, image of USNM slide 124,108." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307556/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">36</figureCitation>
