</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,751,777]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. In contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[487,649,752,777]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submicans">
<emphasis box="[487,649,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. submicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which appears to be fairly widespread in the Caribbean, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaicana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. jamaicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[453,551,792,818]" name="Jamaica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
